  <description><![CDATA[<p>This charming hotel is a well-known landmark in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/f13578bcd0ea422bb13fbbbc34693d47" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f13578bcd0ea422bb13fbbbc34693d47}" title="Amalfi Coast">Amalfi</a>; an old Franciscan monastery converted into a hotel 200 years ago and with a rich history of illustrious visitors.</p>
<p>At the heart of the hotel is the original cloister. Built in the 12th Century, this historic corner offers a lovely, quiet place to relax or read. On the other side of the road perched on the promontory is the watchtower, which houses one of the hotel’s restaurants and has incredible sea views. There are steps down from the tower to the pool located at sea level and you can swim from the rocks here. Guest rooms at the Hotel Luna Convento are all individually decorated in a traditional style, all with superb views over the Mediterranean Sea. Those upgrading to a Superior Room will be able to enjoy those views from their private balcony.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 20 mins by private car from Naples Airport</p>]]></description>
